Directional brain networks were obtained from RS-fMRI data using GC [10], [41–46]. The principle underlying GC [47–50] is as follows: If using the past of time series X improves the prediction of the future of time series Y, then X can be said to have a causal influence on Y [51]. Let X(t) = [x1(t), x2(t),…, xq(t)] be the q selected ROI time series, then the multivariate vector autoregressive (MVAR) model with order p is given by1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
