Betweenness centrality (BC) is a local nodal graph measure that quantifies how much information may traverse the node (any given brain region) and has been widely used in graph analysis [62]. To define the BC measure, let λi(st) be the number of paths [63] between node s and node t, passing through node i. Let the total number of shortest paths between node s and node t be denoted by λ(st). Then, the BC in network D (containing nodes s, t and i) can be defined as4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
